text:
The good: 

--Strong and cheap happy hour margaritas;
--Huge portions of nachos with enough carne asada to make a hungry carnivore very happy;
-- Good salsa;
-- Very nice and attentive staff. No questions asked when I had to send something back. The waiter was very understanding.

The bad: 
-- Mashed black beans on the nachos. Tastes like some kind of paste. 

The ugly: 
-- "Ole Mole" cheese enchilada:  the cheese was cold and the flavor was inedible. Again, mashed black beans. Can't we have a choice, like good old fashioned pinto beans? 

I'd come back for margaritas and chips for sure.
